CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 30, 1954, pg. 28 reads: "March Of Dimes Workers' Tea - Hundreds of Pittsburgh mothers and housewives took part Wednesday night in "March of Dimes" house-to-house solicitation for funds. Prior to the drive, Hill District workers met at the home of Mrs. Eunice Cook for refreshments and last minute instructions.  Seated are Mrs. Alice Thomas, Mrs. Eunice Wright Cook and Mrs. Gladys Brown.  Left to right standing: Elizabeth Jones, Beatrice Wills, Harriett Johnson, Mary Lewis Bennett, Mildred Brown, Princess Mitchell, Carrie Holmes, Flora Godfrey, Mary Martin, Harriett McDonald and Mary Ethel Tyler. -  Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of fourteen women, seated left to right; Alice Thomas, Eunice Wright Cook, and Gladys Brown, standing left to right; Elizabeth Jones, Beatrice Wills, Harriett Johnson, Mary Lewis Bennett, Mildred Brown, Princess Mitchell, Carrie Holmes, Flora Godfrey, Mary Martin, Harriett McDonald and Mary Ethel Tyler, gathered in Eunice Cook's home
